{"outcome":{"note":{}},"detail":"## Report: Issue #30 — Add GradeNA constant and Unsupported field\n\n### Project at a glance\n\n| Fact | Detail |\n|------|--------|\n| **Module** | `github.com\/iksnae\/code-certification` |\n| **Language** | Go 1.25.5 |\n| **Test command** | `go test .\/... -count=1` |\n| **Size \/ Risk** | xs \/ low |\n\n---\n\n### Target file 1: `internal\/domain\/dimension.go`\n\nThe `Grade` type is defined as `type Grade int`. The existing grade constants use an `iota` block:\n\n```go\nconst (\n    GradeA      Grade = iota \/\/ 0 → \"A\"   (0.93+)\n    GradeAMinus              \/\/ 1 → \"A-\"  (0.90+)\n    GradeBPlus               \/\/ 2 → \"B+\"  (0.87+)\n    GradeB                   \/\/ 3 → \"B\"   (0.80+)\n    GradeC                   \/\/ 4 → \"C\"   (0.70+)\n    GradeD                   \/\/ 5 → \"D\"   (0.60+)\n    GradeF                   \/\/ 6 → \"F\"   (< 0.60)\n)\n```\n\nThe `gradeStrings` map (line ~91) drives `Grade.String()`:\n\n```go\nvar gradeStrings = map[Grade]string{\n    GradeA: \"A\", GradeAMinus: \"A-\", GradeBPlus: \"B+\",\n    GradeB: \"B\", GradeC: \"C\", GradeD: \"D\", GradeF: \"F\",\n}\n```\n\n`Grade.String()` checks the map, falling back to `fmt.Sprintf(\"Grade(%d)\", g)` for unmapped values — so today `Grade(-1).String()` would produce `\"Grade(-1)\"`, but adding `GradeNA: \"N\/A\"` to the map will make it `\"N\/A\"`.\n\n`GradeFromScore()` maps score ranges to grades (A through F only). The issue explicitly says **do not change** this function.\n\n**What needs to happen here:**\n\n1. Add a **separate const block** (not inside the iota block — that would shift all existing values): `const GradeNA Grade = -1`\n2. Add `GradeNA: \"N\/A\"` to the `gradeStrings` map\n\nBecause `GradeNA` has value `-1`, it sits outside the 0–6 iota range and cannot collide with any existing or future iota constants.\n\n---\n\n### Target file 2: `internal\/domain\/record.go`\n\nThe `CertificationRecord` struct (line ~65) currently has these field groups:\n\n- **Identity**: `UnitID`, `UnitType`, `UnitPath`\n- **Policy**: `PolicyVersion`\n- **Result**: `Status`, `Grade`, `Score`, `Confidence`, `Dimensions`\n- **Evidence**: `Evidence`, `Observations`, `Actions`\n- **Timestamps**: `CertifiedAt`, `ExpiresAt`\n- **Metadata**: `Source`, `RunID`, `Version`\n\nThere is **no existing `Unsupported` field**.\n\n**What needs to happen here:** Append `Unsupported bool` to the struct. A zero-value `bool` defaults to `false`, so all existing code that constructs `CertificationRecord` literals without this field will continue to behave identically.\n\n---\n\n### Downstream impact assessment (no changes required)\n\n| Area | File(s) | Impact of GradeNA | Impact of Unsupported |\n|------|---------|-------------------|----------------------|\n| **Record store** | `internal\/record\/store.go` | `parseGrade()` (line 515) maps A–F only; unknown strings fall back to `GradeF`. \"N\/A\" would currently map to `GradeF` — that's fine for now per issue scope. `toJSON`\/`fromJSON` use `rec.Grade.String()` which would round-trip \"N\/A\" → `GradeNA` if `parseGrade` were updated, but that's out of scope. | JSON serialization uses `recordJSON` intermediate struct — `Unsupported` won't be serialized unless the intermediate struct is updated (out of scope). |\n| **Override applier** | `internal\/override\/applier.go` | Unaffected — works with `CertificationRecord` by value. | Compiles fine; zero-value `false` means no override-eligible units change behavior. |\n| **Agents** | `internal\/agent\/architect*.go`, `workspace_snapshot*.go` | Grade distribution uses `.Grade.String()` — `GradeNA` would appear as \"N\/A\" if ever used. | All `CertificationRecord` literals in tests use named fields selectively; new bool field defaults to `false`. |\n| **Reports** | `internal\/report\/*.go`, `internal\/workspace\/report.go` | String-based grade comparisons (`\"F\"`, `\"D\"`, etc.) won't match `\"N\/A\"` — safe. | Unaffected. |\n| **CLI commands** | `cmd\/certify\/certify_cmd.go`, `report_cmd.go` | `result.Record.Grade.String()` and `gradeEmoji()` — `\"N\/A\"` would fall through the emoji switch (no match), producing no emoji. Safe. | Unaffected. |\n| **Workspace aggregate** | `internal\/workspace\/aggregate.go` | Already uses the *string* `\"N\/A\"` for `OverallGrade` (a `string` field, not `domain.Grade`). Adding `GradeNA` doesn't collide. | Unaffected. |\n| **Tests** | `*_test.go` | `TestGrade_String` tests only A–F; `TestDimensionScores_Grade` tests `GradeFromScore` (A–F). No existing test covers `Grade(-1)`. Both compile and pass as-is. | All `CertificationRecord` literals use partial field initialization; the new `Unsupported` field defaults to `false`. All compile and pass. |\n\n---\n\n### Concrete instructions for the implement phase\n\n**File: `internal\/domain\/dimension.go`**\n\n1. After the existing `Grade` const block (which ends with `GradeF`), add:\n   ```go\n   const GradeNA Grade = -1\n   ```\n2. In the `gradeStrings` map literal, add the entry:\n   ```go\n   GradeNA: \"N\/A\",\n   ```\n\n**File: `internal\/domain\/record.go`**\n\n3. Append `Unsupported bool` to the `CertificationRecord` struct — after the existing `Version int` field (the last field) is the cleanest spot:\n   ```go\n   \/\/ Unsupported indicates this unit is in an unsupported language and was short-circuited.\n   Unsupported bool `json:\"unsupported,omitempty\"`\n   ```\n   (The `json` tag with `omitempty` ensures it won't appear in JSON output when `false`.)\n\n**Neither change requires touching scorer.go, pipeline.go, report files, `GradeFromScore`, or any existing constants.**\n\n**Verification:** `go test .\/... -count=1`","at":805852695.410437,"phase":"decompose","ticketId":"30","id":"30-1277"}
